  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I stop my Jamster subscription from charging me money?",
  "response": "To stop your Jamster subscription from charging you money, you typically need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Locate Your Subscription Information**: Find your customer reference number or subscription details. This information is usually provided in the confirmation messages or emails you received when you first signed up for Jamster.\n\n2. **Access the Jamster Website or App**: Go to Jamster's official website or open their app if they have one. Sign in using your account credentials.\n\n3. **Navigate to Subscription Management**: Look for a section like \"My Account,\" \"Subscription Management,\" or \"Settings\" where you can manage your subscriptions.\n\n4. **Cancel the Subscription**: Follow the prompts to cancel your subscription. There should be an option to stop your subscription and prevent further charges.\n\n5. **Contact Customer Support**: If you cannot find the cancellation option online, you might need to directly contact Jamster\u2019s customer service. Look for their contact details on their website or in any communications you received from them.\n\n    - **Phone Number**: Call the customer support phone number provided on the website.\n    - **Email**: Use their customer support email to request cancellation.\n    - **Live Chat**: If they have live chat support, this can often be an immediate way to get assistance.\n\n6. **Confirm Cancellation**: Make sure you receive a confirmation of the cancellation, whether via email or on their website. Keep this confirmation for your records.\n\n7. **Check Your Billing Statements**: Monitor your billing statements to ensure no further charges appear after you have canceled the subscription.\n\n8. **SMS Unsubscription**: Sometimes, subscriptions like this allow you to unsubscribe via SMS. Send a keyword like \"STOP\" or \"CANCEL\" to the short code number provided by Jamster (usually found in their SMS messages).\n\nIf you continue to have issues, check Jamster\u2019s specific policies and terms and conditions or escalate the matter through higher-level customer service or consumer protection agencies if necessary.",
